3:["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Bluefin calculates funding rates hourly based on the premium between INJ perpetual and spot prices across integrated price feeds. The institutional-grade matching engine processes funding settlements automatically at each hour mark with sub-second finality on Sui. Funding rates are determined by the 8-hour time-weighted average premium, then divided by 8 for hourly payments. Long positions pay when rates are positive, shorts pay when negative, with direct peer-to-peer settlements between traders."}]
4:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":["Why ","INJ","/","USDT","?"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"INJ/USDT funding rates often deviate significantly from other exchanges due to Injective's unique position as an app-specific blockchain for DeFi. The pair's moderate volume on Bluefin creates arbitrage opportunities against larger CEX platforms like Binance and OKX. Cross-chain arbitrage potential exists as INJ bridges between Ethereum, Cosmos, and Injective networks affect price discovery."}]]}]
5:["$","section","0",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"INJ Funding Rate Patterns"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"INJ funding rates typically range from -0.1% to 0.2% daily, with higher volatility during major DeFi protocol launches on Injective. Positive rates dominate during bull markets as leveraged longs accumulate INJ for governance and staking rewards. The 8% annual staking yield creates baseline demand that keeps funding rates elevated compared to non-staking assets. Weekend periods often show reduced funding volatility due to lower institutional trading activity."}]]}]
6:["$","section","1",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Arbitrage Opportunities"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Bluefin's hourly funding versus 8-hour cycles on major CEXs creates systematic arbitrage windows. INJ's cross-chain nature allows arbitrageurs to exploit price differences between Ethereum-based DEXs and Injective native markets. The relatively low volume on Bluefin means funding rates can deviate 0.05-0.15% from Binance during high volatility periods. Sophisticated traders monitor INJ ecosystem announcements as they often precede funding rate spikes of 24-48 hours."}]]}]
7:["$","section","2",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Risk Considerations"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Sui network risks include potential validator issues affecting settlement finality and the ecosystem's early-stage development compared to Ethereum L2s. INJ's correlation with broader Cosmos ecosystem tokens can create unexpected funding rate movements during ATOM or IBC-related events. Bluefin's lower liquidity means larger positions may face slippage when closing arbitrage trades. Cross-chain bridge delays when arbitraging against other networks can expose traders to funding rate reversals during the transfer period."}]]}]
8:["$","$Ld",null,{"items":[{"question":"How does Bluefin's hourly funding compare to other exchanges trading INJ?","answer":"Bluefin settles funding every hour while most CEXs use 8-hour cycles, creating 8x more frequent cash flows. This can benefit arbitrageurs who can capture smaller, more frequent rate differentials rather than waiting for larger 8-hour settlements."},{"question":"What makes INJ funding rates unique on Sui-based Bluefin?","answer":"INJ rates on Bluefin reflect both Injective Protocol fundamentals and Sui ecosystem growth. The combination often creates rate premiums during cross-chain DeFi narratives when both networks see increased adoption simultaneously."},{"question":"How do Injective's staking rewards affect funding rate arbitrage?","answer":"INJ's 8% staking yield creates persistent long bias, keeping funding rates positive more often than typical perpetuals. Arbitrageurs must account for this structural premium when calculating expected returns versus non-yielding assets."},{"question":"What are the main risks of INJ arbitrage on a Sui-based DEX?","answer":"Primary risks include Sui network validator stability, early ecosystem development phase, and potential bridge delays when arbitraging cross-chain. Lower overall liquidity also means position sizing must be carefully managed to avoid adverse selection."}]}]
